s1452: Twenty-one. Came to court. Died, no heir, state abolished.
s1470: Guangchuan initially established, capital at Xindu.
s1476: Linjiang initially established, capital at Jiangling.
s1484: Divided Chu and reestablished Lu state.
s1497: Third month, Jiaoyin day, initial king Xian Wang De first year. Son of Emperor Jing.
s1498: Third month, Jiaoyin day, King Pengzu first year. Son of Emperor Jing.
s1499: Zhongshan initially established, capital at Lunu.
s1504: Third month, Jiaoyin day, initial king Yanyu first year. Son of Emperor Jing.
s1505: Third month, Jiaoyin day, initial king Fei first year. Son of Emperor Jing.
s1506: Third month, Jiaoyin day, initial king Yu first year, son of Emperor Jing.
s1508: Third month, Jiaoyin day, King Ding Fa first year. Son of Emperor Jing.
s1512: Sixth month, Yihai day, King of Huaiyang relocated to Lu first year. This is King Gong.
s1517: Eleven. Rebelled, executed. Made into commandery.
s1518: Eleven. Rebelled, executed. King Zhi of Jibei relocated to Zichuan eleventh year. This is King Yi.
